5:
*sigh* That was hopefully the last
one.
9:
Where are they all coming from, and
what could they be after?
13:
It shouldn't be possible for the
poppets to disobey me...
17:
This is the third time they have
attacked us. Do you not have any
clue what their goal is?
22:
Obviously not! This has never
happened before.
26:
First Grey disappears, and now this.
Something must be wrong...
29:
You keep mentioning this Grey
person. Who exactly is he?
34:
Grey is, well, Grey! He's a fairly old
man who serves as my retainer...
39:
Guess there's no chance that he
could be Simon then, huh?
43:
The only other person we ran into
was a young man named Simon. He
claimed to be your servant and
asked us to look in on you.
47: I've never met a Simon in my life!
51:
But he definitely said that he knew
you.
55:
Like I said, this is my first time ever
speaking with any people besides
Grey!
58:
None of this makes sense... I don't
know what's happening with Mosnia
either, since the prince's letters
stopped coming.
62:
That Mosnian prince of yours... Is he
from the Kingdom of Mosnia?
66:
You've heard of it then?! Do you
know if there's trouble brewing over
there?
70:
...The Kingdom of Mosnia fell to ruin
300 years ago.
72:
In truth, we're standing in former
Mosnian territory at this very
moment. The royal castle ruins
should be somewhere near this
forest.
76:
That's not possible. I was
corresponding with their prince up
until recently.
81:
About that... Was Grey the one
always handing those letters to you?
84: Yes, but... What are you suggesting?
88:
I should really organize these letters.
It's so hard to tell which ones are
more recent when they're mixed like
this.
91:
"The murash flowers are finally in
bloom this year. I hope one day
soon I can show you the sight of
their magnificent petals lining our
streets."
94:
Do they really expect me to believe
that Mosnia didn't exist this whole
time?
96: That... these letters were all a lie?
99:
I wonder what you'd say if you could
speak.
103:
They HAVE to be mistaken, right?
Otherwise my whole life would've
been a complete lie!
108: Why does my chest feel so tight...
110:
Grey told me to wait here, because
one day delegates from our home
country would come to collect me.
112: I'd finally fulfill my role as princess...
119:
We ended up having to stay the
night.
122: But now what do we do?
126: I have a question about Prika.
128: Do you think she's been lying to us?
137:
Gonna agree with Stella here. She
doesn't strike me as the conniving
type.
143:
She herself is not lying, but she is
surrounded by falsehoods.
145:
I'm curious about this Grey person,
but we should speak with Simon first
and find out what he knows.
149:
I feel like we should bring Prika with
us, but that might be kinda difficult...
153:
Whatever are you going on about?
We require her presence to
expediate the discussion!
156:
First things first, I shall go awaken
our sleeping beauty. Will the rest of
you care to join me?
168:
Were you trying to leave without
saying a proper goodbye to your
host? How rude!
172:
My apologies, Prika. We didn't mean
to be impolite.
180:
Well... We wish to pay Simon another
visit and ask him to clarify a few
matters
185:
Perfect! I was just thinking of seeing
him myself!
188:
If I'm lucky, he might even know
where Grey is!
192:
That's why you're going to take me
to see Simon!
197:
Good morning, my tardy princess! I
do sincerely hope you have had
something other than potatoes for
breakfast!
202:
What? How can I be tardy if we
never agreed to meet up
beforehand?
206: All right, Prika. You are free to join us.
